<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Home Page</title>
  <style>
    body {
      background-image: url('your-image-path.jpg');
      background-size: cover; /* makes the image cover the whole page */
      background-position: center; /* centers the image */
      background-repeat: no-repeat; /* prevents repeating the image */
      margin: 0; /* optional: remove default margin */
      height: 100vh; /* make sure the body takes full viewport height */
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
  <p>This is the home page.</p>
  <a href="about.html">Go to About Page</a><br>
  <a href="contact.html">Go to Contact Page</a>
</body>
</html>
How to customize:
Replace 'your-image-path.jpg' with the actual path or URL to your background image.
You can also add the CSS into an external stylesheet if preferred.
Example with external CSS:
Create a file called styles.css:

CopyRun
body {
  background-image: url('your-image-path.jpg');
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  margin: 0;
  height: 100vh;
}
And link it in your HTML:

CopyRun
<head>
  <!-- other tags -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
</head>
